channel.title: 562 js5 error
channel.description:
Hey guys i used the autocache downloader but when i run my client i get this error: [code]error_game_js5crc [/code]
Yes, i used the correct link. And yes my server is running. I have no clue on how to fix this. Any help?

item.title: 562 js5 error
item.dc:creator: @jaruanna jaruanna
item.description:
@jaruanna wrote:

I’m pretty sure i dl the right cache. Is it supposed to be around 70mb? Also, here is my client settings part of where it should download and where it is downloading from:

public static String getCacheDir() { return System.getProperty("user.home") + "/.CACHE562"; //only change this if you edit cache } public static final String cacheLink = "http://www.mediafire.com/?zgwy0c2rv9pec00"; //make sure it zip public static final int cacheRevision = 4; //change this if you edit cache

And it is a zip file. Forgot to mention that.

item.title: 562 js5 error
item.dc:creator: @Native1 Native^
item.description:
@Native1 wrote:

crc means checksum. So there’s something wrong with the checksum of the client’s cache and the checksum of the update server. Maybe you didn’t download the whole cache. Or forgot the unzip it.
